<F P=101> Bulgaria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Turbogenerator Failure Shuts Down Kozloduy Unit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Turbogenerator Failure Shuts Down Kozloduy Unit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1806144894 Sofia BTA in English 1334 GMT 18 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1806144894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sofia, June 18 (BTA) -- Forty-two minutes after 
midnight the 440-MW Unit One of the Kozloduy nuclear power plant 
was switched off because of a turbogenerator failure, Ms 
Yordanka Stoyanova, head of the Public Relations Department told 
BTA. It was a short circuit in the conventional equipment and 
has nothing to do with the reactor's safety. No radiation 
changes have been registered. The unit was switched on again 
about noon. It will work at about 50 per cent of its capacity 
until the turbogenerator is repaired. Three of the six units of 
the plant are currently in operation. Their capacity totals 
about 1,600 MW. Units Four and Five are undergoing routine 
repairs. 

</TEXT>

