<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Bulgaria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Stance on FYROM Census Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Stance on FYROM Census Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2006193694 Sofia BTA in English 1738 GMT 20 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2006193694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Geneva, June 20 (BTA) -- Bulgaria's permanent 
representative at the United Nations Valentin Dobrev briefed 
international mediators on former Yugoslavia Lord David Owen and 
Thorvald Stoltenberg on Bulgaria's position on the forthcoming 
census in Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia 
-- FYROM]. Bulgaria's representatives at the Council of Europe 
in Strasbourg and at the United Nations and other international 
organizations in Vienna provided similar information to the 
Council of Europe and the Conference on Security and Cooperation 
in Europe (CSCE). 
  The major points of the Bulgarian position, as reported by a 
Foreign Ministry spokesman, are the following: 
  At this stage European standards applied by the Council of 
Europe, the CSCE and other international institutions, 
especially concerning the free expression of national identity, 
are much higher than those operative in Macedonia likely to be 
applied at census; the Government of Macedonia should take the 
necessary steps to secure free expression for all its citizens, 
in line with European standards; Bulgaria will take a stand on 
the results accordingly; Bulgaria attaches great importance to 
relations with Macedonia and is willing to promote them further. 

</TEXT>

