<H3> <TI>   PRC Delegation Visits; Relations Discussed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PRC Delegation Visits; Relations Discussed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1706193394 Sofia BTA in English 1834 GMT 17 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1706193394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sofia, June 17 (BTA) -- Consultations between 
Bulgaria and China were held today at the Foreign Ministry, BTA 
learned from the Ministry's spokesman. Deputy Foreign Minister 
Dimitur Ikonomov headed the Bulgarian delegation, and the 
Chinese delegation was led by Assistant Foreign Minister Qin 
Huasun. The sides discussed cooperation between the two 
countries within the framework of the United Nations and issues 
of common interest included in the preliminary agenda of the 
49th Session of the UN General Assembly. Special attention was 
paid to the reorganization of the world organization and its 
role in settling regional conflicts and peacekeeping operations. 
  The two delegations exchanged views on the sanctions 
enforced 
on certain countries by resolutions of the UN Security Council, 
on various aspects of the UN activities in the sphere of human 
rights, on disarmament issues, etc. 
  The Chinese delegation was received by Foreign Minister 
Stanislav Daskalov. Besides the issues on the agenda of 
bilateral consultations, they discussed Bulgarian-Chinese 
relations in general. 

</TEXT>

