<F P=101> Hungary </F>
<H3> <TI>   MSZP, SZDSZ Reach Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    MSZP, SZDSZ Reach Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2106112794 Budapest MTI in English 1823 GMT 20 Jun 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2106112794 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 20 June (MTI) -- A preliminary agreement 
on the distribution of ministerial portfolios was reached during 
Monday's [20 June] round of coalition talks between the 
Hungarian Socialist Party (MSZP) and the Alliance of Free 
Democrats (SZDSZ), SZDSZ Chairman Ivan Peto announced today. 
  According to Peto, the SZDSZ will provide the minister of 
the 
interior, as well as the transport, telecommunications, water 
management, and education ministers. The rest of the portfolios 
will be held by Socialist politicians. 
  The political state secretary for the Ministry of Education 
will be a Socialist, while Free Democrats will hold the 
political state secretary posts at the Ministry of Industry and 
Trade, and the Ministry of Agriculture. The two parties earlier 
agreed that they would operate 12 ministries. 
  The posts within parliament were distributed 
previously:The speaker of parliament will be a Socialist, and 
one deputy speaker of the three will be a Free Democrat.Free 
Democrats will head three parliamentary committees: the 
constitutional, the defense, and the foreign affairs 
committee.The rest of the non-opposition committees will be 
chaired by Socialists. 
  According to an earlier decision, about one third of 
parliamentary committees will be chaired by opposition parties. 

</TEXT>

