<H3> <TI>   HZDS, Slovak Farmers Party Sign Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    HZDS, Slovak Farmers Party Sign Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1706202594 Prague CTK in English 1724 GMT 17 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1706202594 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Jedlove Kostolany, west Slovakia, June 17 (CTK) -- A 
coalition agreement on election cooperation was signed by the 
chairmen of the Movement for a Democratic Slovakia (HZDS) and 
the Slovak Farmers' Party (RSS), Vladimir Meciar and Pavel 
Delinga, today. 
  The agreement provides for nine RSS representatives to be 
placed on the HZDS list of candidates. The two parties have 
agreed to form a joint deputies' group in the new parliament, 
Meciar reported. The elections are scheduled for September 
30-October 1. 
  First and foremost, it is necessary to ensure that the 
elections are held, Meciar said. After them, Meciar wants to 
acquire such a position which would make it possible for him to 
undertake fundamental changes in the Constitution and economic 
structure of society, he said without specifying. According to 
the latest polls, the HZDS would reap 29 percent of votes, thus 
leading popularity ratings. 

</TEXT>

