  [Text] Bratislava, June 17 (CTK) -- Some 29 percent of 
Slovaks would vote for former premier Vladimir Meciar's Movement 
for a Democratic Slovakia (HZDS), a poll conducted by the Slovak 
Statistical Office in June revealed. About twenty percent of 
Slovaks favor the governing Democratic Left Party (SDL) and 8 
percent the Christian Democratic Movement (KDH). 
  The five-percent border necessary for entering the 
parliament 
would be also crossed by the coalition of ethnic Hungarian 
parties Egyutteles and Hungarian Christian Democratic Movement 
(MKDH) with 8 percent and Premier Jozef Moravcik's Democratic 
Union with 6 percent of votes. The voting turnout would be 77 
percent, while 10 percent of voters have not made up their mind. 

