<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Canadian Soldier Killed, 2 Wounded by Mine </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2106210294 Montreal Radio Canada International in English 
2030 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2106210294 </F>
<F P=104>  Montreal Radio Canada International </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] A Canadian peacekeeper was killed in Croatia 
today [21st June] and two others were wounded. Thirty-one year 
old Corporal Mark Robert Isfield of Chillawack, British 
Columbia, died when a landmine exploded under his armored 
vehicle. Thirty-one year old Sergeant Paul Macmillan of Calgary, 
Alberta, and 35-year old Sergeant Gregory Paul James, also of 
Chillawack, were injured in the explosion. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

