<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Report Outlines Weaponry Destruction Process </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2106114494 Prague RUDE PRAVO in Czech 16 Jun 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU2106114494 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague RUDE PRAVO </F>
<F P=105>  Czech </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [CTK report in the "By Telex" column] </F>
  [Text] The destruction of 167 Czech Army artillery systems 
has been confirmed by a Danish inspection team. This 
information was released on Wednesday [15 June] by the Defense 
Ministry Press Department. In accordance with the Treaty on 
Conventional Armed Forces in Europe, 813 of the 1,062 tanks; 775 
of the 1,032 armored combat vehicles; 778 of the 1,293 artillery 
systems; and 36 of the 50 combat aircraft have been destroyed in 
the former CSFR, and subsequently in the Czech Republic, since 
17 August 1992. 

</TEXT>

