<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Foreign Ministry Protests"] </F>
  [Text] In regard to the latest incidents on the Macedonian 
[The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM]-Yugoslav 
border, involving usurping the place Cupino Brdo and imprisoning 
a Macedonian soldier by Serbian troops, the Macedonian Foreign 
Ministry sent a note of protest to the Yugoslav Foreign 
Ministry, against such behavior of the Yugoslav Army, which 
violates the Macedonian border, creating conditions for heavy 
consequences. At the same time, the Macedonian Foreign Ministry 
demanded an urgent session of the representatives of the two 
countries' foreign ministries, to agree on undertaking steps to 
definitely determine the border line. The Macedonian side 
underlined such negotiations would present basis for development 
of mutual trust, communication, and cooperation between the two 
nations. 

