<F P=106> [Report by Mladen Bosnjak] </F>
  [Text] The session of the Assembly of the Republic of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina and the Constitutional Assembly of the 
Federation of Bosnia-Herzegovina opened at 1200. The first part 
of the assembly session will be held behind closed doors. 
  Today's agenda for the session of the Assembly of the 
Republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina envisages a debate on the report 
by the state delegation of Bosnia-Herzegovina on the Geneva 
peace negotiations, the election of the reshuffled Government of 
the Republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina, and the examination and, we 
believe, adoption of the proposal on the law on ministries and 
other administrative bodies of the Republic of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  The session of the Constitutional Assembly of the Federation 
of Bosnia-Herzegovina will examine the proposal on the rules of 
procedure for the work of the Federal (?Assembly), ratify the 
Government of the Republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina as a federal 
government, and discuss the proposal on the law on ministries 
and on [word indistinct]. 
  This is all from today's session of the assemblies of the 
Republic and Federation of Bosnia-Herzegovina. We shall resume 
reporting as soon as the session is opened to reporters, that 
is, for a live relay. 

