<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Muslims Accused of Shelling Doboj, Teslic </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Muslims Accused of Shelling Doboj, Teslic </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2106213294 Belgrade TANJUG in English 2108 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2106213294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pool" item] </F>
  [Text] Doboj, June 21 (TANJUG) -- Thirteen civilians, 
including five children, were seriously wounded, and many more 
received light injuries in a Moslem artillery attack on the Serb 
towns of Doboj and Teslic in northern Bosnia on Tuesday [21 
June], Bosnian Serb military sources said. The tank and rocket 
shells severely damaged civilian objects in these two 
neighbouring towns, the sources said. Moslems started shelling 
the two towns several weeks ago. 
  Continuing to violate the Geneva Accord on a cessation of 
hostilities which was reached on June 8, the Moslems heavily 
attacked also some other Serb towns, villages and positions in 
the wider area of Doboj. Southeast of Doboj, on Mt. Ozren, 
Moslems opened mortar fire on the Serb villages of Boljanic, 
Karanovac and Petrovo on the left bank of the River Spreca. 
There were no casualties, but the shell explosions caused 
severe material damage to buildings. 
  On the Vozuca front, Moslems are firing at and shelling Serb 
positions and villages along all lines of separation. A Moslem 
troop build-up has also been observed. Moslems are also 
attacking Serb positions east and west of Doboj, but Serbs are 
abiding by the Geneva Accord and open fire only when the lives 
of their troops and civilians are threatened, the Bosnian Serb 
military sources said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

