  [Text] Petrovac, 21 Jun (TANJUG) -- Radio Velkaton of 
Velika Kladusa this evening denied claims made last night by 
Muslim Radio Sarajevo that forces loyal to Alija Izetbegovic had 
arrived at the perimeter of the Agrokomerc agricultural complex, 
that they were successfully advancing towards Polje and Velika 
Kladusa, and that Fikret Abdic had "disappeared in an unknown 
direction." Radio Velkaton said that the army of the Autonomous 
Province of Western Bosnia is firmly in control of all 
separation lines and that Izetbegovic's forces "will never make 
it to Velika Kladusa." 
  The same source said that "the remnants of the 5th Corps" of 
the Muslim army loyal to Alija Izetbegovic this afternoon 
continued their fierce attacks against positions and civilian 
targets in the autonomous province of western Bosnia and added 
that the heaviest infantry clashes and mortar exchanges are 
taking place in the Caglica, Todorovo, and Pecigrad areas. 
According to the radio, these attacks were repelled without 
loss. 
  Radio Velkaton claims that units of the 5th Corps are 
regrouping and redeploying, which means that there will be no 
peace in this region for a long time to come. 

</TEXT>

