<H3> <TI>   Exchange Agreed To Aid Search for Dead, Missing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Exchange Agreed To Aid Search for Dead, Missing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2106213594 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
2000 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2106213594 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Representatives of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army and 
the Croatian Defense Council [HVO] have met in Mostar. They 
agreed to allow up to 200 people cross from the Muslim to the 
Croat bank of the Neretva. Each side will try to locate the 
bodies of dead and missing persons, and reports will be drawn up 
to this effect at places where prisons and unmarked graves are 
still believed to exist. 

</TEXT>

