<H3> <TI>   Government Blamed for VMDK's Internal Crisis </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Blamed for VMDK's Internal Crisis </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1706201394 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1700 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1706201394 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to the Democratic Community of Hungarians 
in Vojvodina [VMDK], the Hungarian political leadership can also 
be blamed for the VMDK's crisis. The VMDK Presidium's 
communique says that following the financial scandal that broke 
out some months ago, the Hungarians in Vojvodina have got into 
an unprecedented political crisis. There are also external 
reasons, namely leading Hungarian politicians, in the background 
of the crisis, the document reads. According to the VMDK 
leaders, some powerful people of the Hungarian Government made 
the financial support aimed for the Vojvodina Hungarians subject 
to a demonstration of party loyalty. The aim of the Hungarian 
Government politicians was to line up the VMDK, too, among the 
supporters of the Budapest coalition. 

</TEXT>

