<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Clinton Visit Considered Summit Opportunity </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Clinton Visit Considered Summit Opportunity </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2206084094 Warsaw GAZETA WYBORCZA in Polish 22 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> WS2206084094 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw GAZETA WYBORCZA </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by "krzem": "Clinton With the Ten"] </F>
  [Text]President Clinton's July visit to Warsaw will be an 
opportunity to hold a ministerial regional summit meeting of 
East and Central Europe. Minister Andrzej Olechowski said 
yesterday that he and U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher 
have invited foreign ministers of nine countries -- the Visegrad 
Group, Albania, Bulgaria, Romania, Macedonia, and Slovenia -- to 
come to Warsaw on 7 July. Bill Clinton will be in Poland on 6 
and 7 July. Among other issues, the ministers will discuss the 
region's security, including "Partnership for Peace," and their 
countries' relations with NATO. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

