BFN 

  [Text] The Sejm Social Policy and Health Commissions have 
come out in favor of including contraceptives on the list of 
medicines for which only 30 percent of the price has to be paid. 
They have also come out in favor of introducting sex education 
in schools and of withdrawing handbooks containing inadequate 
sex information. Today the commissions are discussing 
implementation of the laws on family planning and conditions 
permitting abortion. The deputies have adopted the text of 
recommendations for the prime minister, for which they demand 
government implementation. 

