<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Federal </F>
<H3> <TI>   Popovski Denies FYROM Borders Violated </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Popovski Denies FYROM Borders Violated </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2106160694 Belgrade BORBA in Serbo-Croatian 21 Jun 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> AU2106160694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade BORBA </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [BNA TIKER report: "Statement That the Yugoslav Army Has </F>
Been Pushed Back Is Ridiculous"] 
  [Text] Belgrade (BNA TIKER) -- A statement by Macedonian 
[The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM] Defense 
Minister Vlado Popovski that the Macedonian Army has pushed back 
the Yugoslav Army from certain posts within the FRY [Federal 
Republic of Yugoslavia] is more of a political statement 
intended for the Macedonian public then a serious approach to 
the normalization of relations between the two neighboring 
countries -- TIKER has learned unofficially at the FRY Defense 
Ministry. 
  The Yugoslav Army border patrols are situated exclusively on 
the territory of the FRY and have not on a single occasion 
entered Macedonian territory. The same sources claim that the 
activities of the Macedonian Armed Forces have been observed in 
the vicinity of the border, but the Yugoslav Army will not react 
unless the FRY's sovereignty and territory integrity are 
endangered. 
  Yugoslavia and Macedonia do not share a state border but 
merely an administrative border. The border problems will be 
resolved when a mixed commission goes into the field and marks 
the border with stone markers, UNPROFOR [UN Protection Forces] 
in Skopje says. 
  An UNPROFOR observer team has already been deployed on the 
border crossing between the FRY and Macedonia near Kriva Palanka 
for 12 days. Some 10 Blue Helmets are monitoring the activity 
of the FRY soldiers, UNPROFOR spokesman in Skopje Elizabeth 
Baldwin told TIKER. Macedonia has presented its maps to us and 
it claims that this is its territory, Elizabeth Baldwin says. 
She added that Yugoslavia did not present its maps to UNPROFOR 
even though it was requested to do so. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

