  [Text] Deputy Prime Minister Grzegorz Kolodko has ended his 
visit to the United States, during which he explained to his 
U.S. partners the Polish Government's economic program. 
Grzegorz Kolodko believes that he has succeeded in convincing 
representatives of the Washington government and the IMF that 
the present Polish Government is not wrecking what their 
predecessors have done and that the Strategy for Poland program 
is the plan for the future. 
  [Begin Kolodko recording] The IMF, Treasury Secretary 
Dentsen, and Ms. Tyson, head of President Clinton's team of 
economic advisors, who will visit Poland together with the 
president, all believe that this ambitious program and its 
objectives will be fulfilled and implemented if the work is well 
organized and if government policy is clear and firm, which we 
are, of course, determined to pursue. [end recording] 
  [Announcer] Grzegorz Kolodko has also announced plans to set 
up a Polish-U.S. investment fund to support the privatization 
process in Poland. Deputy Prime Minister Kolodko hopes that 
initially it will be possible to make $100 million available for 
the fund. 

