<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Albania </F>
<H3> <TI>   FRY Embargo Affecting Private Enterprises </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    FRY Embargo Affecting Private Enterprises </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2206083394 Tirana ATA in English 1017 GMT 21 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2206083394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Malesi e Madhe, June 21 (ATA) -- During the 
1992-1993 period a great number of enterprises have been created 
and established economic and trade relations with Montenegro, 
according to the Taxes Office of the Shkoder district. But the 
cooperation of those enterprises did not succeed because Albania 
is observing the UN Security Council economic embargo against 
the Federative [as received] Republic of Yugoslavia. 
  Consequently, the number of the private enterprises which 
exercise their activity in Malesi e Madhe district has decreased 
to 92 having 553 employed persons. A concrete example of the 
embargo's influence is the Vatnikaj Enterprise which had 100 
workers before the UN decision for economic embargo against 
former Yugoslavia. All the workers have now left this 
enterprise and Vatnikaj is close to bankruptcy. 

</TEXT>

