  [Text] Prague, June 21 (CTK) -- In a meeting with Spanish 
Senate President Juan Jose Laborda, Czech parliament Chairman 
Milan Uhde today welcomed the possibility that both chambers of 
the Spanish parliament could ratify the association agreement 
signed between the Czech Republic and the European Union (EU) 
this year. A delegation of the Spanish Senate arrived here 
yesterday for a four-day visit. Uhde said Spanish politicians 
had supported the Czech Republic's aspirations to become a 
member of Western European structures. After a meeting with 
Laborda, Czech Deputy Premier Jan Kalvoda told CTK that Laborda 
said he was convinced the Spanish parliament would approve the 
association agreement in autumn without any problems. 

