BFN 

  [Text] Prague June 22 (CTK) -- Representatives of the 
Liberal Social Union (LSU) and the Bohemian-Moravian Centre 
Party (CMSS) have agreed on their parties' merger by the end of 
September, LSU Chairman Frantisek Trnka said at a press 
conference today. The new party is likely to be named the 
Bohemian-Moravian Centre Union, Trnka said. The opposition CMSS 
and LSU have 9 and 8 deputies in the 200-seat Czech parliament 
respectively. 

