<F P=103> AU2106115094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest ROMPRES, 20/6/1994 -- Oliviu Gherman, the 
president of the Romanian Senate met Monday, 20 June, with the 
president of the Parliament of the Republic of Moldova, Petru 
Lucinschi. 
  The guest presented the situation in the Republic of Moldova 
at the moment, and expressed the view that in the question of 
his country's relations with Romania one should be able to 
overcome the emotional approach and replace it with a pragmatic 
attitude. The sides agreed on the necessity of developing 
closer parliamentary ties forged through direct contacts between 
the standing committees of the two legislative bodies. 
  The president of the Romanian Senate, Oliviu Gherman, also 
met Monday, 20 June, with the president of the Grand National 
Assembly of Turkey, Husamettin Cindoruk. 
  Messrs. Gherman and Cindoruk approached matters regarding 
the 
bilateral ties and the activities of the economic cooperation of 
the Black Sea, with a stress on the prospects the parliamentary 
assembly of this organization offers to the member states. 
  The sides agreed that if willing to develop long-lasting 
economic relations, the partners must base their actions on a 
firm political will for cooperation and understanding. The 
political stability of the member countries, the guest 
underlined, will ensure the economic stability as a natural 
consequence. Mr. Cindoruk emphasized that everything must be 
done to stop the conflict between Armenia and Azerbaijan, while 
ensuring the unity of Georgia. 

</TEXT>

