<H3> <TI>   PUNR Sides With Opposition on Education Law </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PUNR Sides With Opposition on Education Law </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2206091694 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1444 GMT 21 Jun 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2206091694 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest ROMPRES, 21/6/1994 -- During the Tuesday, 
21 June, debates in the plenum of the lower house [Chamber of 
Deputies] the National Romanian Unity Party [PUNR] took the side 
of the opposition when voting for an amendment that stipulates 
that the state budget must apportion at least 4 percent of the 
gross domestic product (GDP) to education. 
  Finance Minister Florin Georgescu in agreement with Dan 
Martian, the leader of the ruling Social Democracy Party of 
Romania [PDSR] parliamentary group, objected to the stipulation 
by law of the percentage allotted to education and sustained 
instead the amendment proposed by Dan Martian, which only spells 
that the real growth of the GDP ratio apportioned to education 
is compulsory, without specifying it. The 1994 state budget law 
earmarked 2.7 percent of the GDP to education. 

</TEXT>

