<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, June 22 (ATA) -- On its way to Romania, the 
Albanian delegation led by the speaker of the parliament, Pjeter 
Arbnori, stopped over in Skopje on June 18 and had a meeting 
with the speaker of the Macedonian Parliament, Andov. Mr. 
Arbnori stressed that frequent meetings are important because 
they help strengthen the relations and open new ways for 
cooperation. 
  Mr. Andov expressed the readiness of the Macedonian party to 
follow this road, with the aim that the relations between the 
two countries must set an example to the Balkan peninsula. 
  Further on Mr. Arbnori expressed some concerns with regard 
to 
the red tape obstacles related with the census of the Albanian 
population, about which he was informed in the meetings that he 
had had with Albanians in Tetovo. Mr. Arbnori asked from Mr. 
Andov to use his authority to help in the quickest and 
satisfactory possible solution of the problems that have aroused 
in the process of the census of the population in The Former 
Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia [FYROM]. 
  Mr. Andov promised and guaranteed the Albanian party a quick 
solution. Further on, Mr. Andov focused on the promotion of the 
economic and trade relations between the two countries which is 
important for the Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia in the 
conditions of the blockade imposed by Greece. Mr. Arbnori 
expressed the readiness and interest of Albania in this point, 
stressing that Albania is ready to go ahead in this direction 
not because the problem is related with Greece but because 
cooperation and the intensification of regional trade and 
economic relations is the only road towards stability and 
prosperity. 

</TEXT>

