BFN 

  [Text] Elbasan, June 21 (ATA) -- The Normalisti 
Association, an organization of Elbasan retired teachers, 
recently organized a rally in support of the education in 
Kosova, against the repression and blackmail of the Serbian 
regime toward the students, teachers, cultural and educational 
institutions of Kosova. Retired teachers, students and teachers 
of the Aleksander Xhuvani University as well as intellectuals of 
different professions participated to this rally. 
  Speaking at the rally, Kristaq Mullisi, chairman of 
Normalisti, said that the situation in Kosova is grave and 
tragical especially in education, culture, and science. He 
considered the situation in Kosova is an unprecedented case in 
the history of the nations of Europe. Mr. Mullisi also 
expressed his solidarity with the teachers, pupils, and all the 
Kosova intellectuals for their mature and brave approach being 
always determined in their right and noble work. 

</TEXT>

