  [Excerpt] The outgoing prime minister and the HSP 
[Hungarian Socialist Party] and SZDSZ [Alliance of Free 
Democrats] leaders have agreed that the current economic 
directors of Hungarian Television and Hungarian Radio should be 
entrusted with the management of the two bodies on a temporary 
basis. The HSP and the SZDSZ are preparing to form a government 
coalition. The three politicians' explain their decision by the 
need to avoid a leaderless state of affairs in the two national 
media institutions. 
  This is contained, among other things, in the government 
communique published after the morning meeting of Peter Boross 
[outgoing prime minister], Gyula Horn [HSP candidate for the 
post of prime minister] and SZDSZ Chairman Ivan Petoe. [passage 
omitted] 

