<H3> <TI>   Kukan Lauds Syrian Role, Views Syria's Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kukan Lauds Syrian Role, Views Syria's Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2206153894 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1115 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2206153894 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague--Slovak Foreign Minister Eduard Kukan has 
asserted that Syria is a primary and important state in the 
Middle East and that, without Syria, a just and comprehensive 
peace cannot be achieved. 
  In a statement to a SANA correspondent in Prague today, 
Kukan 
added that his country appreciates the Syrian policy aimed at 
achieving a just and comprehensive peace in the region. He also 
emphasized Slovakia's support for the peace process, which is 
based on both the UN resolutions and international legitimacy. 
  The Slovak minister stressed the depth of Syrian-Slovak 
relations, which have always been fruitful in all fields. He 
said his coming visit to Damascus on the day after tomorrow, 24 
June, aims to promote and consolidate the traditional relations 
between Syria and Slovakia in a way that will serve both 
friendly countries. 

</TEXT>

