<F P=106> [TA SR report: "Communist Party of Slovakia: Celebrations of </F>
Slovak National Uprising Anniversary, Elections, and Politics"] 
  [Text] Zvolen--The 18 June meeting of the Communist Party 
of Slovakia [KSS] Central Committee approved a proposal to hold 
the communist celebrations of the 50th anniversary of the Slovak 
National Uprising on 20 August in Holic, in the presence of 
representatives of the Communist Party of Bohemia and Moravia. 
The KSS Central Committee also approved the party's electoral 
manifesto, the submitted KSS slate of candidates for the 
parliamentary elections, and the election staff. KSS Chairman 
V. Dado will be the Communists' main leader in the coming 
elections. The meeting also dealt with cadre issues--M. Zozulak, 
J. Sevc, and Anton Porubsky were elected KSS deputy 
chairmen--and assessed some aspects of domestic and foreign 
policy. The KSS Central Committee resolutely protests against 
Zbigniew Brzezinski's call that nuclear weapons be used against 
the DPRK if necessary. It regards Russia's pressure actions and 
the U.S. efforts to impose an embargo as interference in the 
internal affairs of a sovereign state. 

</TEXT>

