  [Text] At its extraordinary meeting today, Prime Minister 
Jozef Moravcik's Cabinet did not approve the wording of the 
agreement to be concluded between the Governments of the Slovak 
Republic and the Russian Federation on the debts of the former 
Soviet Union owed to our country. In spite of this, Deputy 
Prime Minister Brigita Snognerova will leave for Moscow this 
afternoon to hold talks with her partners. Jozef Trojak, state 
secretary in the Finance Ministry, and Anna Jostiakova, director 
of the trade policy department in the Ministry of Economy, are 
also part of the delegation. 

