<H3> <TI>   Army Builds `Strategic' Road in Zenica Area </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Builds `Strategic' Road in Zenica Area </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2206193494 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2206193494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Semso (Luka) from Zenica] </F>
  [Excerpt] Every new road is of strategic interest these 
days, both from the military and from the civilian point of 
view. That is why the members of the Zenica Engineering 
Battalion had cause for pride today, as they officially 
announced that a new road has been marked out, and it will be 
used for bringing in supplies more quickly and safely to our 
defense lines, for taking care of the wounded, and also for 
linking up the existing [word indistinct] between important 
points in Zenica and the neighboring municipalities. 
  Midhat Ibrahimagic, commander of the Engineering Battalion, 
stressed today in front of his soldiers-builders that the 
marking out of this road -- 3,600 meters long, passing through 
inaccessible terrain and under the worst of weather conditions, 
in only 10 days -- was a real achievement. The order from Army 
General Staff has thus been carried out, and the next task on 
surfacing and [words indistinct] until the road is completed 
will most certainly be done within the deadline. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

