<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Clashes between the soldiers of the Fifth Corps 
[Bosnia-Herzegovina Army] loyal to the Muslim authorities in 
Sarajevo and the forces of the Autonomous Province of Western 
Bosnia [APZB] were resumed this morning with undiminished 
intensity, particularly in Caglica in the municipality of Velika 
Kladusa and in Mutevelici and Pecigrad in the Cazin 
municipality, local media of both warring sides have reported, 
without mentioning the casualty toll. 
  According to Serb intelligence sources, 68 APZB and 36 Fifth 
Corps soldiers were killed over the past five days in fierce 
inter-Muslim clashes. 
  According to Muslim Radio Bihac, about 400 APZB soldiers 
were 
captured during the latest inter-Muslim clashes. 

