<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Abdic Reportedly in Control, Fighting Continues </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Abdic Reportedly in Control, Fighting Continues </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2306143794 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1245 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2306143794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Petrovac, 23 Jun (TANJUG) -- Radio Velkaton of 
Velika Kladusa denied this morning's REUTER report that members 
of the Muslim army's Fifth Corps, loyal to Alija Izetbegovic, 
"deeply penetrated" the territory controlled by Fikret Abdic and 
that Abdic's "days are numbered." 
  The radio said forces of the National Defense of the 
Autonomous Province of Western Bosnia [APZB] are firmly in 
control of all separation lines in the Cazin Krajina. 
  This afternoon members of the Fifth Corps continued their 
ferocious attacks on civilian targets and positions held by APZB 
forces, Radio Velkaton said. 
  According to the same source, heavy fighting is under way in 
the area of Pecigrad and the strategically important point 
Pivka. One member of the APZB army was killed in the fighting, 
while another three were wounded. 
  Radio Velkaton claims that Izetbegovic's artillery units 
pounded the areas of Porcici, Veljkovici, and Liskovac, 
inflicting considerable material damage. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

