BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Katarina Andric] </F>
  [Excerpt] The republican commissioner for refugees today 
held a news conference for foreign and domestic correspondents. 
There were several topics on the agenda: the revision of the 
refugees' status in Serbia, humanitarian operations, and 
cooperation with other international humanitarian institutions. 
The correspondents were addressed by Bratislava Morina, 
commissioner for refugees. Katarina Andric reports: 
  [Andric] There are approximately 500,000 refugees in the 
Republic of Serbia. The majority of them live with Serbian 
families. The greatest number of refugees are women and 
children. Almost 200,000 of them are under 18 years of age, 
1,200 children are without parental care, and 10,000 babies have 
been born in exile. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

