<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serb Police Continue To Harass Albanians </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2206210194 Tirana TVSH Television Network in Albanian 1800 
GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2206210194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana TVSH Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Albanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The deployment of military trucks, Serb police 
punitive expeditions, and raids and harassments are still being 
carried out in various parts of Kosova. 
  In the Kodra e Trimave Quarter in Prishtina at approximately 
1600 [1400 GMT] yesterday, a convoy of military vehicles from 
Podujeve paraded along the main street of this quarter and then 
headed toward the center of Prishtina. The convoy was made up 
of ambulances and armored military cars. 
  Meanwhile, a police expedition with four [word indistinct], 
two armored cars, seven police cars, two Land Rovers, and one 
excavator entered the Korish village in Prizren and reeked havoc 
among the peasants. This police expedition raided several homes 
and harassed Ajet Mucaj and his mother Elmaze. They also opened 
holes [vrima] in Mucaj's yard under the pretext of searching for 
weapons. 
  The Kosova Information Center reports that raids and 
maltreatments have been reported in Podujeve, Mitrovice, 
Skenderaj, Kline, and Lipjan. 

</TEXT>

