<H3> <TI>   Black Sea Conference Concludes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Black Sea Conference Concludes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2206205394 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1900 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2206205394 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>
<F P=105>  Romanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The proceedings of the third session of the 
Parliamentary Assembly of Black Sea Economic Cooperation, which 
have been held for two days at Bucharest Parliament Palace, 
concluded today. 
  This afternoon, the new leadership was elected. Aleksandr 
Moroz, president of Ukraine's Rada was elected president of the 
assembly. Mr. Vladimir Kovalev, head of the Russian Federation 
delegation and deputy president of Russia's State Duma, and 
Afayedin Zhalilov [name as heard], head of the delegation from 
Azerbaijan, were elected deputy presidents. Mr. Osman Seif of 
Turkey, member of the Judicial and Political Commission of the 
assembly, was elected treasurer. 

</TEXT>

