<F P=100> ALBANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhulali, Turkish Delegation Discuss Cooperation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zhulali, Turkish Delegation Discuss Cooperation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2206203994 Tirana TVSH Television Network in Albanian 1800 
GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2206203994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana TVSH Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Albanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A Turkish military delegation led by Deputy Defense 
Minister General Toman Erkan arrived in Albania today. General 
Erkan was received by Defense Minister Safet Zhulali, who 
welcomed him and wished him a pleasant stay in Albania. 
  Then a meeting was held, in which Minister Zhulali appraised 
the relations and cooperation between the two countries in the 
field of defense and paid tribute to Turkey's contribution to 
the education and training of personnel, as well as its 
assistance in various fields. 
  Mr. Zhulali went on to stress that, in view of its 
modernization and Partnership for Peace, our army requires more 
help and stronger support in the fields of communication, food, 
medicine, the military industry, etc. 
  For his part, after conveying greetings from the Turkish 
defense minister to Zhulali, General Erkan confirmed that Turkey 
would help the Albanian Army in accordance with the bilateral 
agreement. The cooperation and support that we render to the 
Albanian Army, he said, is a question of mutual assistance. 
  Metin Ornekol, the Turkish ambassador to Tirana, attended 
the 
meeting, which took place in a warm atmosphere. 
  In addition to other activities, the Turkish military 
delegation held working meetings with Lieutenant General Ilia 
Vasho, chief of the Army General Staff, Deputy Defense Minister 
Bashkim Shehu, and other top officials to pinpoint possible 
avenues for greater assistance to the Albanian Army. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

