<H3> <TI>   Romania's Nastase, Russia's Kovalev Hold Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Romania's Nastase, Russia's Kovalev Hold Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2206194194 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1634 GMT 22 Jun 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2206194194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest, ROMPRES, 22/6/1994 -- Adrian Nastase, 
speaker of the Chamber of Deputies, met with Valentin Nikolayev 
Kovalev, vice president of the State Duma of the Russian 
Federation, and the head of his country's delegation to the 
third plenary session of the Parliamentary Assembly of the Black 
Sea Economic Cooperation Organization, hosted by the Romanian 
capital. 
  The sides agreed that there were no delicate issues between 
the two countries of a nature to hinder a real and wide 
expansion of the mutual relations, both sharing the conviction 
that, through their activities, the two legislative fora could 
best serve the mutual interests and economic exchanges between 
their countries. They underlined the importance of finalizing 
the negotiations on the framework political treaty between 
Romania and the Russian Federation. 
  Adrian Nastase accepted to visit the Russian Federation next 
autumn. 

</TEXT>

