<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kovalev Views Economic Development </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kovalev Views Economic Development </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2206193994 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1557 GMT 22 Jun 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2206193994 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest, ROMPRES, 22/6/1994 -- The vice president 
of the State Duma (Parliament) of the Russian Federation, 
Valentin Kovalev, told a press conference held at the Romanian 
Parliament building that an improvement of the customs 
regulations, blended with the growth of investment in 
international trade would boost by some 15 per cent the 
import-export activities between the countries affiliated to the 
Black Sea Economic Cooperation Organization. 
  Besides these steps, the Russian Federation contemplates 
other means as well for the economic development in this area, 
such as a Black Sea Cooperation Bank, a consolidated 
infrastructure for transports, including a circular auto route 
around the Black Sea, and a unitary power grid in the entire 
zone. 

</TEXT>

