<F P=103> AU2206181294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Varna, June 22 (BTA) -- NATO General Antonio 
Milani, deputy commander-in-chief of Allied Forces Southern 
Europe, today met with Bulgarian Deputy Navy Commander Rear 
Admiral Khristo Kontrov. General Milani has been visiting 
Bulgaria since the start of this week. 
  The sides reaffirmed agreements between the working groups 
of 
the Allied Forces Southern Europe and the Bulgarian Navy Staff. 
The General Staff of the Bulgarian Army will be asked to 
approve a plan for a Black Sea naval exercise under Partnership 
for Peace in June or July 1995. It will be attended by four to 
eight NATO ships deployed in the Mediterranean. The 
participants will practice rescuing a ship in distress, struggle 
with fires and flooding water, evacuation of wounded people, etc. 

