<H3> <TI>   NATO To Establish Military Base Near Komarom </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NATO To Establish Military Base Near Komarom </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2206161794 Budapest MTI in English 1431 GMT 22 Jun 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2206161794 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 22 Jun (MTI) -- Having provided 
scientific and methodological help to support the environmental 
rehabilitation of former Soviet military facilities in 
East-Central Europe, NATO now wants to set up a reference 
military base in order take the process one step further. 
  According to preliminary plans, the base would be built on 
the military facility near the town of Komarom (N. Hungary), 
which Soviet troops used for nearly half a century. The new 
base will provide scientific training for experts, and display 
various methods for environmental protection. 
  The plan was disclosed in Komarom on Wednesday [22 June], 
when NATO members from the division of science and environmental 
protection, who are currently holding talks in Hungary, visited 
the heavily polluted facility. Construction will be carried out 
by NATO's environmental protection section and the joint 
research centre of the Budapest Technical University and the 
State University of Florida. 

</TEXT>

