<H3> <TI>   Government Approves New Wage Restraint Policy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Approves New Wage Restraint Policy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2206092194 Prague CTK in English 1900 GMT 21 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2206092194 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, June 21 (CTK) -- Wage growth limits in 
1994 will be 10 percent for loss-making companies and 12 percent 
for profit-making companies, according to a resolution approved 
by the Slovak Government today. 
  During the first quarter, wages in loss-earning companies in 
Slovakia grew by 15.1 percent in comparison with the first 
quarter in 1993. As many as 2,900 firms with 25 or more 
employees had combined losses of ten billion crowns in the first 
quarter. 
  By holding down wages in profit-making firms the government 
is attempting to prevent wage increases in the financial, 
banking and insurance sphere. 

</TEXT>

