<F P=103> AU2206185094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pristina, June 22 (ATA) -- The framed trial against 
14 Albanians accused of being members of the "Ministry of 
Defence" of the Republic of Kosova continues in the Serbian 
court of Pristina. 
  The first two accused interrogated, Hajzer Hajzeraj, who 
before abolishment of Kosova's autonomy was deputy minister of 
the People's Defence and commander of the Civil Defence of 
Kosova, and Haxhi Ferati, magistrate of the People's Defence, 
turned down the accusations, saying that there is no "Ministry 
of Defence" of the Republic of Kosova and what is said in the 
charge is but slander. 
  The two accused said that they have been arrested and 
physically and mentally tortured by inspectors of the Serb state 
security in order to obtain statements through violence. 

