<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prague Council To Have 55 Members </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2306191094 Prague CTK in English 1524 GMT 23 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2306191094 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague, June 23 (CTK) -- The next Prague Council is 
to have 55 members, a council meeting agreed today. 
  The local election law says that towns with over 150,000 
people shall have between 35 and 55 council members but when 
towns fail to state the exact number of counselors for the next 
term 85 days before the elections they are only allowed 35 
counselors. 
  The present council, which has 76 members, is yet to 
announce 
the number of districts for the local elections and how many 
counselors will be elected in each district. 

</TEXT>

