<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Melescanu, Olechowski Sign Cooperation Agreements </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2306191294 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1544 GMT 23 Jun 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2306191294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, ROMPRES, 23/6/1994 -- Poland's Minister of 
Foreign Affairs Andrzej Olechowski, and Romania's Minister of 
Foreign Affairs Teodor Melescanu signed Thursday, 23 June, in 
Warsaw several documents regarding the cooperation between the 
two countries. They are two economic agreements: for the 
avoidance of double taxation and prevention of fiscal evasion, 
and, respectively, the mutual promotion and protection of 
investments. The sides also signed a cultural cooperation 
agreement and an accord of collaboration in foreign policy 
matters. 
  The two ministers shared the opinion that the documents 
signed today are apt to relaunch the bilateral relations, 
stagnant for some time. 

</TEXT>

