<H3> <TI>   PAC's Manolescu Views Censure Motion </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PAC's Manolescu Views Censure Motion </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2306185894 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1505 GMT 23 Jun 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2306185894 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest, ROMPRES, 23/06/1994 -- The parties 
grouped under the name of the Democratic Convention of Romania 
(CDR) and the Democratic Party (PD-FSN) have jointly forwarded a 
censure motion, Civic Alliance Party (PAC) President Nicolae 
Manolescu announced at his party's weekly newsbriefing. 
  He made it clear that, unlike other motions, the text of the 
present one no longer blames the government for economic 
mismanagement, but for the failure of having kept its promises. 
  "Very comprehensive" in contents, as the PAC leader 
described 
it, the fresh motion questions Mr. Vacaroiu's Cabinet's entire 
activity. 
  As for the censure motion of the Agrarian Democratic Party 
of 
Romania (PDAR), and the invitation issued to the opposition 
parties to join it, Nicolae Manolescu said the agrarians' 
decision came a little late, but he agreed that most of their 
objections were well grounded. As for the co-signing of the 
agrarians' censure motion, this is out of question, he said, 
because regulations allow for one signature along one 
parliamentary session. 

</TEXT>

