<H3> <TI>   National Democrats Express Support for Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    National Democrats Express Support for Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2406090694 Prague CTK in English 1801 GMT 23 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2406090694 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, June 23 (CTK) -- The National Democratic 
Party (NDS) Executive Committee, at its meeting today, expressed 
full support for Slovak Privatization Minister Milan Janicina, 
an NDS member. 
  An NDS statement given to CTK says that the growing attacks 
on the minister, who is also NDS deputy chairman, from the 
Democratic Left Party (SDL), an NDS coalition partner, were 
unjustified and contradicted the ethics of coalition cooperation. 
  Statements by SDL Chairman Peter Weiss, Chairman of the SDL 
deputies' group Milan Ftacnik and some other deputies about 
Janicina's giving unjustified preference to the coupon method of 
privatization compared with other methods are not qualified and 
substantiated, the statement says. 
  The NDS considers it "natural and moral that citizens, 
through coupon privatization, receive their share in the 
property which they have been creating in the past," the 
statement says. The NDS Executive Committee believes that "the 
coalition government will meet its commitments and offer 
citizens property worth at least 88 billion Slovak crowns (some 
3 billion USD)," it adds. 
  Following unsuccessful attempts by the opposition Movement 
for a Democratic Slovakia (HZDS) to dismiss Janicina there have 
been calls for a change of privatization minister. It is 
primarily the coalition SDL which raises objections towards 
Janicina's performance. There has long been speculation about 
controversies between Janicina and Economy Minister Petr Magvasi 
concerning the concept of privatization. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

