<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Slovakia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Carnogursky Gives Conditions for KDH Slate </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Carnogursky Gives Conditions for KDH Slate </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2306135894 Prague CTK in English 1055 GMT 23 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2306135894 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava June 23 (CTK) -- Only representatives of 
the Permanent Conference of the Civic Institute (SKOI) will be 
placed at the list of candidates of the KDH (Christian 
Democratic Movement), KDH Chairman Jan Carnogursky said after 
the last round of talks about the KDH slate today. 
  The leading figure of the SKOI is former Czechoslovak 
Interior Minister Jan Langos. 
  The governing KDH (18 deputies in the 150-seat Slovak 
parliament and 8-10 percent in polls) had conducted talks with 
several right- wing and centrist parties about their possible 
joint slate. 
  "It was not possible to wait any longer," Carnogursky said 
about the National Democratic Party (NDS) whose representatives 
showed interest in the KDH slate in early June. However, two 
weeks ago, they received a similar offer from Premier Jozef 
Moravcik's Democratic Union (DU) and stopped the talks with the 
Christian democrats. 
  The final version of the KDH slate will be approved on July 
9, Carnogursky reported. 
  The elections will be held on September 30-October 1. 

</TEXT>

