  [Text] President of the Republic of Albania Sali Berisha 
received General Teoman Erkan, Turkish deputy defense minister, 
in a special meeting held today. 
  At the meeting, President Berisha pointed out the 
satisfactory relations with Turkey, including those in the 
military field. He said that the signing of the joint protocol 
and Erkan's visit mark progress in the military cooperation 
between the two countries so as to preserve peace and stability 
in the region. 
  On his part, General Erkan thanked Berisha for the reception 
hosted for him in Albania and said that Turkey was determined to 
further bolster the relations between the two armed forces. 

