<H3> <TI>   SDS Deputies `Infringe' Parliamentary Boycott </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SDS Deputies `Infringe' Parliamentary Boycott </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2306172794 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1500 
GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2306172794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The parliamentary group of the Union of Democratic 
Forces [SDS] decided on its own judgment to infringe the 
parliamentary boycott because of the bill on amending the Law on 
Rehabilitation Victims of Repressions. Stefan Savov, the 
group's chairman, told our reporter Antoaneta Puncheva that when 
a decision -- he clearly had the boycott in mind -- proves to be 
wrong, it has to revoked. 
  Savov has not received any official reaction from the SDS 
National Coordinating Council to the parliamentary group's 
decision, which was reached yesterday. The coalition's 
political organ will discuss the decision at its meeting on 
Tuesday [28 June]. Stefan Savov also denied the rumor that he 
is supposed to become prime minister during the term of the 
present parliament, implying he will be prime minister of a 
caretaker cabinet. I have a big party behind me, he said; I am 
not the kind of politician fit to serve in a caretaker cabinet. 

</TEXT>

