<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Coal Miners Mount Protest Rally in Sofia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Coal Miners Mount Protest Rally in Sofia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2406091094 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1600 
GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2406091094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today coal miners belonging to the KNSB 
[Confederation of Independent Trade Unions in Bulgaria] and 
Podkrepa held a protest rally in Aleksandur Nevski Square in 
Sofia. Representatives of working collectives from the pits in 
Maritsa- Iztok, Troyanovo-1, -2, and -3, the briquette factory 
in Gulubovo, and mines in Pernik, Bobovdol, and elsewhere. The 
miners put forward demands for protecting the national 
coal-mining industry and the drafting of a clear concept for its 
future development. They also demanded the immediate restarting 
of the briquette factory in Gulubovo, which provides fuel for 
more than 2,000 families, and the exemption of its production 
from value added tax, which makes it output unsalable. 
  According to a press release issued by the Council of 
Ministers Press Center, Prime Minister Lyuben Berov and Nikita 
Shervashidze, chairman of the Committee on Power Supply, met 
with representatives of the striking coal miners and power 
industry workers. On behalf of the strikers, the 
representatives handed Prof. Berov a declaration containing 
their demands. The strikers' representatives were briefed on 
the measures adopted today by the government to ensure the 
financial stabilization of the energy industry until the 
introduction of a mechanism for periodically updating the prices 
of energy products. 

</TEXT>

