  [Text] Two Polish soldiers from the UN forces have died and 
two others were injured as a result of a mine explosion in 
Croatia, the spokesman of the United Nations' peace forces 
reports. The incident happened at about 1100 in the northern 
sector of the Croatian territory controlled by the Serbian 
separatists, and which is under the UN forces supervision. The 
UN spokesman has not yet given any details of this incident. 

