<DOCNO> FBIS4-32457 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu122_k_94008" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EEU-94-122 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  22 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN Envoy Visits UNPROFOR Units in Krajina </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN Envoy Visits UNPROFOR Units in Krajina </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2206115894 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1122 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2206115894 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vukovar, 22 Jun (TANJUG) -- Yasushi Akashi, UN 
secretary general's special envoy for former Yugoslavia, and 
General Milan Celeketic, commander of the Serb Krajina army, 
visited units in Slavonia, Baranja, and Western Srem today, 
according to the press center of the Serb Krajina army's main 
headquarters. 
  Yasushi Akashi visited UNPROFOR's units in Beli Manastir and 
Vukovar and General Celeketic visited the zone of responsibility 
of the [Serb Krajina] Slavonia-Baranja Corps as part of his 
regular activities. 
  In a statement for the republic of Serb Krajina television, 
Gen Celeketic gave a positive assessment of combat readiness for 
defense of the republic of Serb Krajina. 

</TEXT>

