<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Albania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Agreements Ratified With Austria, UNHCR </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Agreements Ratified With Austria, UNHCR </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2306182494 Tirana ATA in English 1011 GMT 23 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2306182494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, June 23 (ATA) -- Albanian Parliament 
approved in its yesterday's seance the intergovernmental 
agreement between the Republic of Albania and the Republic of 
Austria, between the Republic of Albania and the UN High 
Commissariat for Refugees, the agreement with the International 
Federation of the Red Cross and Red Crescent. 
  The agreement with Republic of Austria, which comprises 
economic exchanges, defines that for facilitating such a 
relations between the two countries, the two sides will treat 
each-other according to the principle of the most favourite 
nation in regard to customs and other taxes and facilitating the 
relations between the enterprises and organizations and 
associations called "enterprises." This cooperation will mainly 
be promoted in agriculture, forestry economy, chemical industry, 
light industry, energy resources, construction, health and 
environment protection, tourism, exchange of information, taking 
in consideration the legislation in power in the two countries 
which have signed this agreement. 
  The other agreement between the Albanian Government and the 
UN High Commissariat for Refugees (UNHCR) defines the rights and 
the obligation of the two sides. The agreement has 17 articles 
and intends to set the basic conditions for cooperation between 
the UNHCR and the Albanian Government for carrying out the 
international protection and functions of the humanitarian aid 
in favour of refugees. 
  During this seance, the parliament ratified the agreement 
between the Albanian Government and the International Federation 
of the Red Cross and Red Crescent. The agreement creates a real 
opportunity that a delegation of this international federation 
exercise its normal activity and function in conformity to the 
existed laws of the Republic of Albania. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

