<H3> <TI>   Czech Republic's Havel Ends Working Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Czech Republic's Havel Ends Working Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2406090994 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1600 
GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2406090994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Silviya Velikova] </F>
  [Text] Today Vaclav Havel, president of the Czech 
Republic, ended his brief working visit to our country. He held 
talks in private with President Zhelev. At the subsequent news 
conference, both presidents expressed satisfaction with the 
development of Bulgarian-Czech relations, while stressing that 
work in that direction should be pushed forward by various means 
and at various state forums. Presidents Havel and Zhelev also 
discussed the situation in the Balkans, the course of the 
democratic processes in both countries, and the development of 
democratic institutions in them. 
  Prominent Bulgarian intellectuals, Bulgarian and foreign 
journalists, and of course both presidents attended an official 
presentation to launch Vaclav Havel's book "Power of the 
Powerless." 

</TEXT>

