<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Walesa Pledges Confidence in Foreign Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Walesa Pledges Confidence in Foreign Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2306180594 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1714 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2306180594 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 23 Jun--Poland's President Lech Walesa today 
sent a letter to Foreign Minister Andrzej Olechowski, assuring 
him of "the unchanging confidence of the president of the Polish 
Republic in the minister and in the entire Polish foreign 
service." 
  Here is the text of the letter, passed to PAP by the 
presidential press office: 
  ``Minister! 
  ``Polish diplomacy yesterday became the object of a dramatic 
political debate. Many people who have served the Republic well 
and with devotion must today feel bitter and disoriented; can 
they continue to act in the name of the Republic? Can they 
credibly continue to represent it? 
  ``I ask that at this difficult moment you assure these 
persons--all the employees of the Ministry of Foreign 
Affairs--of the unchanging confidence of the president of the 
Polish Republic in the minister and in the entire Polish foreign 
service. 
  "[Signed] Lech Walesa." 

</TEXT>

